metadata.name: Alma de Flor #18
metadata.description:
Alma de Flor is a project inspired by nature and floral afterlife. 

Plants are alive, they grow on our planet and populate almost every continent on earth. 
They live, grow and die. 
Some plants live a long time, some others don't. Kind of like humans, they change and evolve. They have souls, but they're different from ours, they differ in energy. 

Living in a tropical country allowed me to live in a place with huge biodiversity, so for me, this is how a born European, raised Latino person connects with this feeling.

metadata.name: PEGS #345
metadata.description: Taking inspiration from work by Karl Gerstner, Armin Hofmann, Nick Kuder and Dmitri Cherniak, PEGS explores the limits of constrained algorithmic variation. Based on the simple, playful idea of wrapping a string across a board of pegs, it shows how endless possibilities can be achieved with just a basic set of rules and a few primary colors. When done right, generative art challenges us to answer fundamental questions around creativity, beauty, and life itself.

metadata.name: ThetaStar #15
metadata.description:
A "ThetaStar" is generated through an Iterated Function System determined by the fxhash with one main feature 'Theta' corresponding to an angle value in radians sampled uniformly at random in the range 2.5 < Theta < 3.0.

**Click / Touch** the canvas to reset and watch the "ThetaStar" gradually radiate in full spectrum.
The visually daring may **Rapidly Click / Touch** for an enhanced strobe like effect.

metadata.name: Alienpillars #174
metadata.description:
"A rare type of bug that supposedly arrived on a cargo ship is destroying crops on planet Uctumi, in the binary system of Extronium. A wide variety of very resistant subspecies has mutated and it is necessary to study and identify all of them to obtain a gen-activated pesticide that will work on all of their variations. The pest department of the Uctumi central government is working hard on it, and they say that these strange critters are probably related to similar species that inhabited the planet Earth of the Solar system a long time ago and have spread over the galaxy."

My second piece using the p5.js raymarcher I wrote. The drawing is made of circles and lines based on the 3D data. I wanted to try something hairy as it's easy to draw lines aligned to the surface normal with this method. I also used a shader for the frame and the glitchy/sketch features.

Features 

body color: green-red-purple-yellow-blue-black
body tone: dark-light
spots color: orange-green-blue-yellow-white
hair tips: yes-no
hair #1: short-medium-long
hair #2: short-medium-long
head size: small-medium-large
head shape: long-spherical-wide
glitchy mode: 10% chance
sketch mode: 9% chance
